6 §1228.1. Short title
7 This Part shall be known and may be cited as the "Services For Survivors of
8 Sexually Oriented Criminal Offenses Access Act".
9 §1228.2. Findings and purpose
10 A. The legislature hereby finds and declares all of the following:
11 (1) Sexual assault is a serious public health and criminal justice issue that
12 affects individuals of all ages, genders, and backgrounds throughout the state of
13 Louisiana.
14 (2) Timely, high-quality forensic medical examinations by a trained sexual
15 assault nurse examiner, referred to in this Part as "SANE", are critical to ensuring
16 survivor-centered care, collecting forensic evidence, and supporting prosecution of
17 sexual assault offenders.
18 (3) Access to SANE services is uneven across the state, with significant gaps
19 in rural and underserved regions.
20 (4) Establishing a statewide SANE coordinator and regional mobile SANE
21 nurse teams will improve equitable access to forensic nursing services for survivors
22 of sexual assault throughout the state.
23 B. The purpose of this Part is to ensure that every survivor of sexual assault
24 in this state has access to a trained sexual assault nurse examiner regardless of
25 geographic location, and to establish a coordinated, sustainable statewide
26 infrastructure for the performance of forensic medical examinations for victims of
27 sexually oriented offenses.
